Southern California has been hit by severe storms, causing floods, mudslides, and power outages.
In San Bernardino National Forest, cars were stranded in the snow, while residents of Santa Clarita were evacuated due to floods.
Tragedy struck in Los Angeles when a hillside collapsed, burying two people in a tent.
The stormy weather led to road closures, rescues, and chaos across the region.
Union Pacific faced challenges with mudslides and closed rail lines.
The situation remains dire, with ongoing rescue efforts and concerns about the economy.
Winter continues to bring unpredictable weather patterns across the country.
